cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL

The paper deals with computer vision tasks related to autonomous driving, such as segmentation, depth estimation, and 3D bounding box detection. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also mentions the use of the dataset for autonomous driving, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.RO (Robotics). The dataset is annotated with semantic labels, which indicates the use of machine learning algorithms, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely categories as well. Finally, the paper mentions the detection of soiling, which could involve natural language processing techniques, making cs.CL (Computation and Language) a possible category.
